  </head>
<body>
<Nav />

<div class="bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <span style="opacity:.4">/</span>
  <span style="color:var(--text-3)">About</span>
</div>

<main id="main-content">

  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="tag">About the author</div>
      <h1>Luke</h1>
      <div class="hero-role">Shopify Automation Specialist &nbsp;·&nbsp; Founder, Stack Architect</div>
      <p class="hero-lead">I build and document free automation tools for Shopify store owners. Every guide on this site comes from hands-on implementation work — building Make.com scenarios, configuring server-side tracking APIs, and testing deployments on real stores. My tools are used by 500+ stores to replace $700+/month of paid apps at $0.</p>
      <div class="cred-strip">
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Shopify automation specialist</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Make.com · Meta CAPI · Google Enhanced Conversions</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Tools used by 500+ stores</div>
        <div class="cred"><span class="cred-dot"></span>Based in Huddersfield, UK</div>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/stack-architect-6766733b0" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cred cred-link">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="color:var(--g);flex-shrink:0"><path d="M16 8a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v7h-4v-7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2 2 2 0 0 0-2 2v7h-4v-7a6 6 0 0 1 6-6z"/><rect x="2" y="9" width="4" height="12"/><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="2"/></svg>
          LinkedIn
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── BACKGROUND ── -->
  <section class="section-alt">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Background &amp; experience</div>
      <h2>Where this knowledge comes from</h2>
      <p>Stack Architect exists because I kept running into the same problem while helping Shopify store owners: they were paying $149–$299/month for server-side tracking tools that are doing nothing more than routing a <a href="https://shopify.dev/docs/api/admin-rest/2024-01/resources/webhook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify Order webhook</a> through an automation platform. I built the first version of CAPI Shield myself — configuring the <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Conversions API</a> directly via Make.com — and it worked identically to the paid tools at $0.</p>
      <p>That pattern repeated across every category. Inventory management. P&L reporting. TikTok Events API. Email automation. In every case, the paid app was charging monthly for configuration work that takes under 10 minutes to replicate directly. So I documented all of it — step by step, with the exact API endpoints, field mappings, and Make.com scenario structures — and published it free.</p>
      <p><strong>Every number on this site is real.</strong> The Event Match Quality scores (7–8.5) are from real stores' Meta Events Manager. The savings figures are calculated from actual Shopify App Store pricing. The 500+ stores count comes from tracked deployments across four measurable sources — detailed in the methodology section below.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── EXPERTISE ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Technical expertise</div>
      <h2>What I work with directly</h2>
      <p>The guides on this site cover areas I implement hands-on. Here is an honest breakdown of what I actually know vs. what I've referenced from documentation:</p>
      <div class="exp-grid">
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Server-side tracking</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Meta CAPI &amp; Google Enhanced Conversions</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Direct implementation of <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Conversions API</a> and <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9888656" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Enhanced Conversions</a> via Make.com webhooks. Verified EMQ scores of 7–8.5 across UK, US, AU, and CA stores.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Automation</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Make.com &amp; Google Apps Script</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Building <a href="https://www.make.com/en/help/tools/webhooks" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Make.com scenarios</a> for Shopify webhook routing, multi-branch logic, error handling, and retry patterns. Diagnosing and fixing <a href="https://developers.google.com/apps-script/guides/services/quotas" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Apps Script quota errors</a> at volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">Inventory &amp; reporting</div>
          <div class="exp-title">Shopify Webhooks &amp; Google Sheets</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Real-time order logging to Google Sheets via <a href="https://shopify.dev/docs/api/admin-rest/2024-01/resources/webhook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify Order payment webhooks</a>. Live P&amp;L dashboards tracking revenue, COGS, ad spend, and net profit — no BI tool required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="exp-card">
          <div class="exp-label">TikTok &amp; email</div>
          <div class="exp-title">TikTok Events API &amp; Systeme.io</div>
          <div class="exp-body">Server-side <a href="https://business-api.tiktok.com/portal/docs?id=1771100786590721" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok Events API</a> via Make.com — recovering 20–40% of conversions lost to iOS ITP. Migrating stores from Klaviyo to Systeme.io's free plan with full automation parity.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 500+ METHODOLOGY ── -->
  <section class="section-alt">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Methodology &amp; transparency</div>
      <h2>How "500+ stores" is counted</h2>
      <p>The 500+ stores figure appears throughout this site. Here is exactly where it comes from — because a claim without methodology is just marketing copy.</p>
      <div class="methodology">
        <div class="methodology-label">// Verified deployment sources — April 2026</div>
        <p>A store is counted once it confirms deployment of at least one Stack Architect tool. Stores appearing in multiple sources are deduplicated. The count is conservative — it excludes stores that downloaded guides but did not confirm deployment.</p>
        <div class="method-grid">
          <div class="m-item">
            <div class="m-source">Beehiiv newsletter</div>
            <div class="m-desc">Subscribers who clicked a deployment confirmation link in the welcome sequence</div>
          </div>
          <div class="m-item">
            <div class="m-source">Make.com referrals</div>
            <div class="m-desc">Affiliate sign-ups who activated a CAPI Shield, Stocky Swap, or TikTok CAPI scenario</div>
          </div>
          <div class="m-item">
            <div class="m-source">Stripe kit purchases</div>
            <div class="m-desc">Complete Kit buyers — all $29 purchasers receive and activate pre-built scenarios</div>
          </div>
          <div class="m-item">
            <div class="m-source">Support confirmations</div>
            <div class="m-desc">Direct support contacts who confirmed a successful deployment in follow-up</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── TRANSPARENCY ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// How this site works</div>
      <h2>Full transparency</h2>
      <div class="transparency">
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">$</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>Affiliate links fund this resource.</strong> Stack Architect uses affiliate links to Make.com, Systeme.io, Tidio, Gorgias, GetResponse, Beehiiv, and Google Workspace. If you sign up via a link on this site, I may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. I only recommend tools I use myself and have tested on real deployments. Affiliate relationships do not influence which tools are recommended — if a free alternative exists, it is always listed first.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">0</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>The tools are free forever.</strong> No tool on this site has a paid tier or will ever move behind a paywall. The <a href="/pro">$29 Complete Kit</a> is a one-time purchase of pre-built files — four Make.com JSON blueprints and two Google Sheets templates — not a gated version of the free guides. Everything in the kit can be built manually from the free guides.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">✓</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>Numbers are verified against real sources.</strong> EMQ scores (7–8.5) come from real Meta Events Manager screenshots. Savings ranges reflect current Shopify App Store pricing cross-referenced as of April 2026. Conversion recovery percentages (20–40%) match published ranges from <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/conversions-api/using-the-api" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta's own CAPI documentation</a>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-row">
          <div class="t-icon">↗</div>
          <div class="t-text"><strong>External sources are cited throughout.</strong> Where guides reference API behaviour, platform documentation, or third-party specifications, the source is linked directly to the official documentation. Platform pricing and API behaviour change — always verify current details directly with the vendor before deployment.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── TOOLS ── -->
  <section class="section-alt">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="sec-tag">// Free tools on this site</div>
      <h2>What I've built</h2>
      <p>Six free tools, 21 calculators, and a guide library covering every workflow in the free Shopify automation stack. All free forever.</p>
      <div class="tools-list">
        <a href="/capi-shield" class="tool-row">
          <span class="tool-name">CAPI Shield — Meta + Google server-side tracking</span>
          <span class="tool-saving">saves $149–$299/mo</span>
        </a>
